The paper presents an approach to improve the sample complexity for a variety of curve fitting problems, including active learning for linear regression, polynomial regression, and continuous sparse Fourier transforms. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to machine learning and data analysis, such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper involves mathematical optimization techniques, which could place it in sub-categories such as cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
